reviews.review_text: Althea Jerry forgot the words a couple times on Althea but still sounds awesome. But Phil just is awesome on the bass, definitely a good version.
3-2-87 Good show. Great sound. Thanks Charlie.

Great Space Great show, prefer this version to the matrix.
Peace,
Bob

front of board or aud can someone upload an aud version of this show they must be out there   to me this is a smoking Dew love to have it on the road with me.   I give the show 4 starts cause of the space truckin dew.
Excellent second set, good first. Better than previous night.

Awesome show! Digging the Bird Song and Stranger in the first set quite a bit, China>Rider to open the second, and one of those legendary late 80's Morning Dews that Jerry builds up so intensely at the end to close the show. Phil's on fire the whole show, particularly Eyes, and Brent's harmonies are flawless throughout. 4* considering the scale of all GD shows, 5* for this particular "era" of GD shows. 5* for the soundboard quality and CM upgrade. Thanks Charlie for another one! :D

1st Set Closer The Stranger from this show is just unbelievable.  I've never heard one that comes remotely close to this one. The Ramble On Rose and China>Rider are also excellent versions. Although this show is a bit sloppy at times, I give it 4 stars for the stellar sound (thanks, Charlie!) and the songs mentioned above.
Stranger and Stranger By far the best Stranger I have ever heard.  The guitar solo is white-hot.  The rest is good, but not up to that level.
